ies of fundamental questions on the role exercised by the various elements of civil society in Québec, ranging from the relevance of political parties to the diversity of social movements. "Education, Language, and Immigration" delves into developments in long-standing issues at the heart of the challenge of pluralism in Québec. "Territoriality, Globalization, and International Relations" tackles questions faced by every contemporary society and proposes new arenas for research for Québec.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aNationalismzQuébec (Province). 4aCoursebook. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Canadian.2bisacsh1 aAndrew, Marie Mc, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBalthazar, Louis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeauchemin, Jacques, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBernier, Luc, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlais, Andre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCharest, Jean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGagnon, Alain G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGagnon, Alain G., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGagnon, Alain- G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGaron, Francis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGidengil, Elisabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGraefe, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKarmis, Dimitrios, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeating, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLajoie, Andrée, econtributor.